German glass-maker Schott Zwiesel boasts a 130-year-history of innovation and success, including such break-throughs as the first machine-made stemware and the first lead-free crystal glass.     Known for its food-friendly nature, this grape thrives in Austria. This Gr√ºner is medium-bodied with crisp acidity and a very balanced, spicy finish.

  • California: Firestone Santa Ynez Valley Chardonnay
    The most popular white grape of the state, Chardonnay has made a happy home in California. This Chardonnay from Santa Ynez Valley has fresh fruit aromas of Fuji apple and citrus zest, complemented by notes of vanilla, toasted oak and caramel.

  • South Africa: Ken Forrester Petit Chenin Blanc
    Known locally as "steen," Chenin Blanc in South Africa has a crisp, easy drinking style. The Ken Forrester Petit Chenin displays clean, mouthwatering flavors of crisp green apple, quince and pear, with notes of honeysuckle and ripe melon.

  • Italy: Kris Pinot Grigio
    The Italian term for "Pinot Gris," Pinot Grigio exhibits fresh and fragrant aromas, often with a good dose of citrus. Kris offers enticing aromas of acacia flowers, citrus, tangerine, apricots, and hints of almonds.

  • Spain: Bodegas Ramon Bilbao Valinas Albari√±o
